                <p class="font-weight-700">Battery and Range:</p>
                <p>The Activa E features dual swappable batteries (1.5 kWh each), providing a range of approximately 102 km on a full charge​. The QC1 has a fixed battery setup with a slightly lower range suitable for short city rides.</p>
                <p class="font-weight-700">Motor:</p>
                <p>Powered by a 6 kW Permanent Magnet Synchronous Motor (PMSM), the Activa E offers smooth acceleration and a top speed of 80 km/h​.</p>
                <p class="font-weight-700">Display and Connectivity:</p>
                <p>A 7-inch TFT touchscreen offers navigation, smartphone connectivity, and notifications​.</p>
                <p class="font-weight-700">Ride Modes:</p>
                <p>Both models feature three ride modes (Standard, Eco, and Sport) and include a reverse gear for added convenience​.</p>
                <p class="font-weight-700">Expected Price:</p>
                <p>
                    Activa E: ₹1.10–1.40 lakh (ex-showroom)<br />
                    QC1: ₹90,000–1.00 lakh​.
                </p>
                <p class="font-weight-700">Availability:</p>
                <p>Bookings start early 2025, with deliveries expected later in the year</p>
            </div>
        </div>
